definitions.definition: Anything that is produced; a result .
examples: The product of last month's quality standards committee is quite good, even though the process was flawed.

subdefinitions.definition: The amount of an artifact that has been created by someone or some process.
examples: They improve their product every year; they export most of their agricultural production.

subdefinitions.definition: A consequence of someone's efforts or of a particular set of circumstances.
examples: Skill is the product of hours of practice.  His reaction was the product of hunger and fatigue.

subdefinitions.definition: A chemical substance formed as a result of a chemical reaction.
examples: This is a product of lime and nitric acid.

subdefinitions.definition: A quantity obtained by multiplication of two or more numbers.
examples: The product of 2 and 3 is 6.  The product of 2, 3, and 4 is 24.

subdefinitions.definition: Any operation or a result thereof which generalises multiplication of numbers, like the multiplicative operation in a ring , product of types or a categorical product .
Any tangible or intangible good or service that is a result of a process and that is intended for delivery to a customer or end user.

examples: That store offers a variety of products .  We've got to sell a lot of product by the end of the month.

subdefinitions.definition: Illegal drugs , especially cocaine, when viewed as a commodity.
examples: I got some product here — you buying?

definitions.definition: Any preparation to be applied to the hair, skin, nails, etc. Often specifically a preparation used to hold one's hair in a desired arrangement.
examples: Wash excess product out of your hair.

main_definition: Anything that is produced; a result .
secondary_definitions: ( countable , uncountable ) A commodity offered for sale.
( cosmetics , uncountable ) Any preparation to be applied to the hair, skin, nails, etc. Often specifically a preparation used to hold one's hair in a desired arrangement.
